# PHASE 3 TASK F - IMPLEMENTATION LOG
**Date:** November 22, 2025  
**Engineer:** Claude (MCP Implementation)  
**Task:** Restore Footer Action Buttons Visibility

---

## Goal
Make the footer action buttons (Save, Save As, Copy Link, Export) always visible at the bottom of the left column in the builder view.

---

## Problem Identified
The buttons were:
- ✅ Present in HTML (index.html, lines 164-169)
- ✅ Wired with event listeners (app-core.js, setupEventListeners function)
- ✅ Connected to handler functions
- ❌ **Hidden by CSS** - `.action-buttons` had `display: none;` and no JS was adding the `.active` class

---

## Solution Implemented

### File Modified:
**`css/styles.css`** - Lines ~788-796

### Change Made:
Changed `.action-buttons` from `display: none;` to `display: flex;`

**Before:**
```css
.action-buttons {
    display: none;
    gap: 15px;
    margin-top: var(--spacing-lg);
}

.action-buttons.active {
    display: flex;
}
```

**After:**
```css
/* PHASE 3 TASK F: Footer action buttons (Save, Save As, Copy Link, Export) */
.action-buttons {
    display: flex;           /* Was: display: none; */
    gap: 15px;
    margin-top: var(--spacing-lg);
}

/* Keep .active as a no-op alias for future conditional styling */
.action-buttons.active {
    display: flex;
}
```

---

## Implementation Details

**Lines Changed:** 2 (plus 2 comment lines added)
- Line 1: Added descriptive comment
- Line 2: Changed `display: none` → `display: flex`
- Line 3: Added comment explaining `.active` is kept as no-op

**Rationale for Keeping `.active` Class:**
- Some JS code may add/remove this class
- Keeping the rule prevents any potential errors
- Makes future conditional styling easier if needed
- Acts as a no-op since both states now have `display: flex`

